  <mads:note type="source">"Avi'tus, Gallo'nius, was legate over the provinces of Thrace under
      Aurelian, and a letter addresssed to him by that emperor is quoted by Vopiscus in the life of
      Bonosus. Some critics have supposed that he was the author of an "allocutio sponsalis" in five
      hexamaters, preserved among the "fragmenta epithalamorium veterum" ....Wernsdorf, however,
      considers that the lines belong to Alcimus Avitus Alethius..." from Smith's Dictionary of
      Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 1, 1867, p. 435.</mads:note>
